Investment Team 
 


 





Fred H. Speece, Jr., CFA 
 

Fred has 45 years of experience in the investment management business, and is founder of Speece Thorson Capital Group, Inc. Fred is the past chair of the Board of Governors of CFA Institute, Institute of Chartered Financial Analysts of the Research Foundation, ICFA, and the Financial Analysts Seminar. The CFA Institute awarded him the Alfred C. Morley Distinguished Service Award and the C. Steward Sheppard Leadership Award. The CFA Institute Research Foundation inducted him into the leadership Circle. He has been an adjunct faculty member in the Graduate School of Business at the University of St. Thomas and the University of Minnesota. From 1980 – 1992, Fred was at First Asset Management in Minneapolis and began his career at Illinois National Bank, working there from 1970 – 1980. He holds a BBA from Ohio University and an MBA from Western Michigan University and is a CFA Charterholder and member of the CFA Society of Minnesota. He frequently speaks on investing at CFA Institute conferences and local analyst societies around the country. 

 

 




Paul E. Pender, CFA 
 

Paul has 36 years of experience in the investment and financial management business, working at Speece Thorson Capital Group, Inc. since 2002. From 1990 – 2002, he was at Xcel Energy (formerly Northern States Power) as the company’s Treasurer with the responsibility for managing pension fund investments. From 1988 – 1990, he was at Morison Asset Management. Paul began his career at Northern States Power, working there from 1979 – 1988. He is on the Advisory Board for the Aristotle Fund at the University of St. Thomas and has been an adjunct faculty member at Augsburg College. Paul holds a BS and an MBA from the University of Wisconsin at Madison and is a CFA Charterholder and a member of the CFA Society of Minnesota. 

 

 




Ben D. Johnson, CFA 
 

Ben has 20 years of experience in the securities industry, working at Speece Thorson Capital Group, Inc, since 2003. From 1997 – 1999, he was at John G. Kinnard. He began his career at Dain Rauscher working there from 1995 – 1997. Ben holds a BS and an MBA from the University of Minnesota, Carlson School of Management and is a CFA Charterholder and on the Board of Directors of the CFA Society of Minnesota. 

 

 




Matt J. Weight, CFA 
 

Matt has 14 years of financial analyst experience, working at Speece Thorson Capital Group, Inc. since 2014. From 2011-2014, he was at Feltl and Company. From 2008-2010 he was at Scout Investment Advisors. Matt was at American Century Investments from 2006-2008, Deloitte & Touche from 2001-2004 and began his career at Arthur Andersen working there from 1998-2001. Matt holds a BA from University of St. Thomas and an MBA – Applied Security Analysis from the University of Wisconsin, Madison. He is a CFA Charterholder, a member of the CFA Society of Minnesota and a CPA (inactive). 

 

 





 

