About Our Firm
INDEPENDENT
Founded in 1992, we are a privately held money management firm in Minneapolis, specializing in institutional and family asset management.

From left: Fred Speece, CFA; Beth Hickey; Ben Johnson, CFA; Matt Weight, CFA, Paul Pender, CFA; Judy Haeg
COMMITTED
Principals are co-investors, reflecting their commitment to our investment approach and clients.
PHILOSOPHY
We invest in good cultures and good businesses that meet our high standards for "well-managed, financially powerful and attractively priced."
FOCUSED
We focus on a single, time-tested fundamental investment approach: high quality, classical value applied in the mid to small cap sectors of the market.

Separate account management is available with a minimum investment of $5 million.
Commingled management is available to accredited investors in the form of the Speece Thorson Capital Group Value Fund with a minimum investment of $1 million.


ADDING VALUE
Our ability to add value over the index is demonstrated by our:

Long-term investment horizon
Independent research and portfolio management team
Disciplined valuation methods
Concentrated portfolio
In depth knowledge of our companies, their culture, business and management
 
 


 





 


 





 


 





 


 





 


 






 

